    ```javascript
function isCircular(sentence) {
    const words = sentence.split(' ');
    for (let i = 1; i < words.length; i++) {
        if (words[i - 1].slice(-1) !== words[i][0]) {
            return false;
        }
    }
    return words[words.length - 1].slice(-1) === words[0][0];
}
```

    The algorithm is straightforward:
1. We split the input `sentence` into individual strings in an array by using the space character as a delimiter.
2. We iterate through the words in the array, checking if the last character of the previous word is equal to the first character of the current word. If not, return `false`.
3. After the iteration, we check if the last character of the last word in the array is equal to the first character of the first word. If so, we return `true`; otherwise, return `false`.

